As always you report was very nice but this feedback…..Well it’s “disappointing” to put it politely.  The ONE area that I think the whole DAOC community can agree on is that skald defense is just bad and yet this feedback seems to miss that point completely.  <br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This is a very slippery slope. At this time, we're not planning on adding any more defense to skalds, although we do want to keep a close eye on this aspect and understand the concerns. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
This looks to me like someone who is not familiar with melee RvR and how skalds compare to other classes.  I could almost translate this to say “but you have speed and stun and mez to get out of a fight.  Nothing is wrong with you defense.”  If minstrel defense was considering lacking to the point they needed the ablative chant, how in the world could skalds (with the same base armor, less evade and lower dex) be considered a “slippery slope”?  Heck all I wanted was the dodger RA and evade 2.  Lines like<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This is common for many classes and not specific to the skald. With the recent block/parry changes, players should explore the options of making trade offs to raise parry if they want more in the area of melee defense. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
just shows a lack of understanding about our spec options.  If you did “explore the options of making trade offs to raise parry” you would have such a gimp class that every one in DAOC would just pity you.<br>
<br>
As I read this the person responding will 1) raise or DA range, but will do it for wardens and paladins too (nice but does little to help our core issues) 2) look at shouts, this is the only positive thing I see in this message 3) Leave resists alone as he/she does not have the mandate to work on it (being handled by another group) 4) Leave the RA alone because he/she does not have the mandate to work on it.<br>
<br>
Last they STILL have not made a definitive statement on what/who skalds are expected to be.  Are we a support class?  Are we a hybrid?  Why do we have the worse support skill set in the game at the same time we have almost the weakest melee (Damage AND defense) and poor (700) range.<br>
<br>
Not sure who the feedback came from but to be honest it looks like they spent 15 min evaluating your report and 2600 entries in the official thread.  All I can say is that I am glad I am going to be gone most of the summer on work trips and vacation.  Maybe in September things will be better but I need the break with this kind of response.<br>
<br>
Keep up the good work and don’t let this be the final word.  Go over this person/teams head if you have to.  You have more patience than most saints as I think I would have given up months ago.<br>
