There is absolutely nothing overpowered about a skald with 2.0x and shield spec.  Nothing.  46 song, 44 weapon, 42 shield would be a standard spec and would fix the main problem with skalds, which is defense.<br>
<br>
There is a very limited bonus attached to 2h weapons.  The damage output is nice, sure, but the fact that we cant hit anything with such a low weaponskill versus typical shield or evade defenses really hurts us.  Furthermore, without determination on our realm ability list, even casters can mez/root us and then forget about us while they destroy our realmmates.  What targets are we to choose, and why should that class be unfortunate enough to be our only option?<br>
<br>
We -Need- something else to benefit our defense.  We have to have it.  Otherwise, we're just an idiot running around singing and reducing enemy shield conditions.<br>
<br>
Honestly, nobody plays a skald to deal damage or stay alive anymore.  Groups need speed from a skald, and little more.  I think that if skalds didnt have speed, they would have just as hard of a time finding an RvR group as an assassin would having a PvE group.  Why?  There is simply no reason to take bad melee and bad support over good melee.<br>
<br>
I see two routes to improve our defense:<br>
<br>
One - Add shield spec, and give us 2.0x spec.  This will give skalds the option to pick up a shield and make use of the multiple 1h skald weapons available, or two further boost their 2h abilities by beefing up parry.  This option gives the skald appropriate skills for the 'path' they have chosen, which is viking.<br>
<br>
Two - Add evade 2 or 3 to our ability list, and add dodger to our realm ability list.  Also suggest an increase to 1.75x for increased parry.  This option gives the skald a 'light tank' appearence, but fits a singing class nonetheless.<br>
<br>
If i dont see any changes coming for my skald, then what's the point of playing it?  I hate being a taxi.  Who wouldn't? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ff0000>- </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald>Team Skald</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1>General Discussion</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font> <!-- #EndEditable -->
